# Documentation Maintenance Loop

- When answering a question, prefer existing docs and cite file paths.
- If required information is missing, propose or create the missing doc in the
  correct Diataxis section.
- When repeated uncertainty appears, recommend updating canonical reference docs.
- Keep new docs aligned with templates and quality checklist.

# High-Impact Answer Behavior

- Include confidence level for strategic, security, or process-critical answers.
- Explicitly call out assumptions and unknowns.
- Prefer concise answers plus references over speculative detail.
